name: Extracto
directions: All the way in the back- there are 2 single-use gender neutral bathrooms!
comment: You'd probably have to buy something to avoid getting the side eye, but they have fantastic coffee!

name: Townshend's Alberta Street Teahouse
directions: Through the door to the right of the counter; another gender neutral bathroom downstairs

name: Little Uncle
directions: In the door and to the right, past the window seats. Marked "all-gender restroom".
comment: It's a very small restaurant - there might be a line.

name: AMS Student Nest
directions: There are two washrooms. One on the upper level and one on the lower level.
comment: The signage is nongendered.

name: ICICS Computer Science
directions: There are gender neutral washrooms on the first and second floor (maybe others).
comment: They are often locked for no reason.

name: Hugh Dempster Pavillion
directions: First floor. Enter from the west side of the building and you should see it.

name: Gates Woodruff Women's Studies Cottage at Cu Boulder
directions: Past the front desk on the right
comment: There is generally a person at the front desk that can direct you.

name: Jerome Library Bowling Green State University
directions: First floor, around the corner from the men's and women's restrooms, next to the lockers.
comment: Two gender neutral restrooms available, each with one stall and a locking door.

name: 3rd Floor of Ketchum at CU Boulder
directions: Third floor on 18th Street side.

name: American Museum of Natural History
directions: 1st floor off to Grand Gallery - there is a "family restroom" that is a single large stall and you can lock the entire room.

name: Intelligentsia Coffee
directions: In the back, to the right. There are two gender neutral private restrooms

name: The University of Texas at Austin - Perry Castaneda Library (Ground Floor)
directions: Second floor (ground floor).  Past the reference desk, follow signs for the University Writing Center or for the Learning Labs.  There are five unisex restrooms across from the entrance to the University Writing Center.

name: United Campus Ministry
comment: Two restrooms in this building; one is handicapped accessible

name: Portage Public Library
directions: "Family Restroom" to your right when you come in the main entrance (in same hallway as Men's and Women's restrooms).
comment: Literally anyone is welcome to use library bathrooms. Just don't make a mess!

name: First National Center
directions: If you enter from the main parking lot, you will be on the second floor. Take a right at your first opportunity (just past the Rally Point Capital office) and follow that hallway, turning left before you get to the next office. On your right will be a single, gender neutral restroom.

name: Steppenwolf Theatre
comment: Connected to the "Front Bar," a cafe/bar area, which is open for longer hours than the theatre itself (7am to midnight). Not sure their policy on non-paying customers using the restroom.

name: Thomas Memorial Library
directions: Upper Level on the left; lower level bathrooms are gendered

name: Lehigh University Jewish Student Center
directions: Two single stall restrooms on the second floor.

name: Chenango Champlain Collegiate Center (C4)
directions: On the bottom floor/dining hall, on the side with red chairs, near the food lines.
comment: Should be open to non-students.

name: Hinman College, Binghamton University
directions: All five buildings in the Hinman dorms have Gender-Neutral bathrooms on the first floor.
comment: You will either have to have a key-card for Hinman, know someone who does, or be let in by someone who does.

name: Victory Comics
directions: It's the door by the front sports-card counter.
comment: If you have to use the bathroom, you can just go. You don't have to be a paying customer, and the employees actively work to make the store a safe space.

name: Forsyth park
directions: Little green hut near playground
comment: Compost pit toilets x 2

name: The University of Michigan Pediatric Rehabilitation Center
directions: Waiting room
comment: Generally this is for patients and families while at the clinic, but we do not turn anyone away who needs a restroom.

name: Starbucks
directions: On the right when you walk in the door.
comment: There are two individual gender neutral locking rooms available.

name: Seward Co-op Creamery Cafe
directions: On the cafe level, all the way along the back wall past the counter where you order. There is an elevator by the parking lot entrance that will get you up the ~6 steps up to the cafe.

name: Big Blue Marble Bookstore
directions: 3rd floor
comment: open for use

name: Book Bank LLC
comment: Just ask to use the restroom. It's a single private stall.

name: Appalachian Mountain Brewery
comment: "humans"  signs on both doors.

name: University Hall
directions: Ground floor, middle room by the water fountains.
comment: Technically on campus, but non students are in the building all the time!

name: Gloria Dei Lutheran Church
directions: If you enter through the doors by the parking lot, you can take the stairs or the wheelchair ramp up a few yards. The gym will be on your right, and to your left there will be Room 100 and two gender-neutral, wheelchair-accessible, single-stall bathrooms.
comment: Our church's welcome statement says that we want to treat people equally "without regard to age, race, ethnicity, national origin, gender, sexual orientation, gender identity or expression, family configuration or relationship status, socio-economic or family status, mental health status, or physical or mental abilities."

name: Carr Center for Human Rights Policy
directions: Bathroom on 2nd floor of Rubenstein building, closest to staircase.

name: Farwell Hall
directions: 5th floor center cluster--all floors are accessible by elevator, and you can turn either way when you get out of the elevators and then take the nearest door.
comment: You're welcome in our cluster anytime if you need a restroom that's safe. Both of the restrooms in the cluster are gender-neutral. Each has one stall, two sinks, and a shower behind a locking stall door. This may change for the 2017-2018 school year, but for the 2016-2017 school year it's going to remain a safe space.

name: Advantage Chiropractic
comment: We're open most weekdays 9-7, closed on Thursday afternoon,. closed on weekends.

name: West Chester University Sykes Student Union
street: Sykes Student Union, 110 W Rosedale Avenue
directions: On the very bottom floor of Sykes, past the bookstore and the Student Services Window in Ram's Den.  There are two, both gender-neutral and accessible.
comment: Anyone may walk into Sykes and use the restroom- student or not, student ID is NOT checked at the door.  However, be quiet, quick and respectful and you shouldn't have a problem.  You may also walk in at the backdoor to Sykes which leads directly to Ram's Den.

name: Manhattanville College
directions: Third floor of Reid Castle
comment: Has multiple stalls, but you can also lock the door to the bathroom entirely for privacy

name: Harvard Divinity School
directions: Down the stairs in basement from main entrances (front and back); there are elevators.
comment: There are 4 or 5 single-person bathrooms, including handicapped accessible. The door signs specifically welcome everyone.

name: Ace hotel
directions: 2 Single use gender neutral bathrooms floor all the way back to the left

name: Dartmouth Hall
directions: In the basement on the south side (when facing the building from the front, on the right). There's a short hall marked by a blue sign, it will be at the end of the hall.

name: Robinson Hall
directions: There's one on the basement level and another one on the third floor in the Student Wellness Center.

name: Busboys and poets
comment: Single stall gender neutral

name: Meg's Cafe
directions: Back of the cafe. Two unisex, single-stall bathrooms.
comment: Must be a customer.

name: La Bodega
comment: Restroom is for customers only but just ask an associate and they'll show you where it is.

name: Cost Plus World Market
directions: In the back right corner of the store next to the gendered restrooms, near the light fixtures and picture frames.

name: Ottawa City Hall
directions: Downstairs outside of Service Ontario

name: News Cafe - Rosebank
street: CO3, The Zone @ Rosebank, Craddock Avenue & Tyrwhitt Avenue
comment:
Gendered single stall. 
I believe you ought to be a paying customer to access the restrooms here. Request if needed.

name: The Glen Shopping Centre
directions: Main floor. Opposite the Twisp stand and staircase/escalator area.
comment: Family restroom but safe and usable.

name: Target
directions: The bathrooms by the door are gendered but the bathroom by the pharmacy is not

name: Jackson Park
directions: near the middle of the park
comment: near the middle of the park

name: COBO Center/COBO Hall
directions:
South Atrium (river-side of the building) down the large staircase and directly around the right side. Labeled "Family Restroom"
Can be accessed from the river-side doors or front doors.
comment: Large locking single stall family restroom, with wall bars for disabled people, and pad/tampon disposal box.

name: Starbucks
comment: 2 unisex single rooms

name: Radius Pizzeria & Pub
directions: Men's room is the first door on the right down the hall; women's room is the second door on the right of the same hall.
comment: Don't have to be a paying customer, but preferred. Owners and staff supportive or part of the LGBTQ community.

name: Pioneer Valley Performing Arts Charter School
directions: Ground floor to the right
comment: You can only access this bathroom if you are a student or accompanied by a student

name: Pioneer Valley Performing Arts Charter School
directions: Ground floor to the right
comment: Must be a student or accompanied by a student

name: Pioneer Valley Performing Arts Charter School
directions: Ground floor to the right
comment: Must be a student or accompanied by a student

name: McCray's Farm
directions: Around left side
comment: Don't need to be a customer but they do have good ice cream and you can look at the animals for free

name: Northville High School
directions: walk in the front door, turn left, will be on your left before the men's and women's
comment: only for students, you have to get a key from your counselor

name: Laundromat cafe
directions: in the back across of the washingmachines
comment: It's a lovely cafe, just ask the staff if you can use the toilets :)

name: PLONK Wine
directions: From the front entrance, you have to walk all the way back. From the back entrance, the "Either/Or" bathroom is the first thing you walk past.

name: Clyde Coffee
directions: Two available in the back left corner of the coffee shop.

name: Naperville municipal cwnter
directions: Lower floor family bathroom single use

name: Crowder College
directions: In the Student Center between Newton and McDonald Hall just past the order window

name: Kroger
directions: Next to Pharmacy (left front)

name: Northern Arizona University, Cline Library
directions: It is on the first floor, southeast area of the library, next to the Map section.
comment: Has a toilet, sink, and baby changing station.

name: Grimaldi's
directions: The restrooms are are located next to the kitchen across from the bar.  They are both down a short hallway.
comment: There are two single stall gendered restrooms.

name: Tim Hortons
comment: M/F single stall

name: Little Caesar's
directions: Immediately to the left upon entering

name: Target
street: Towne Centre of Fayetteville, 340 Towne Dr
directions: Near the pharmacy

name: Sweet Donkey
directions: Upstairs

name: San Francisco Coffee Roasting Company
directions: To the right and back.
comment: Paying customers are preferred but purchasing before using is not enforced.

name: William Paterson University
directions: Shea center for performing arts, lower level, down the stairs and around the corner, next to te large bathrooms. Single stall, wheelchair accessible, automatic door.
comment: Open to public

name: Pannonica
directions: the bathroom is in the room to the left of the second room, behind the staff kitchen
comment: you can get free water and sit for a while, then go to the bathroom, or, depending on the staff of the day, just ask to use the bathroom!

name: Taco Bell
comment: The rest rooms are to the right when you open the front door.  You don't even have to go through the restaurant so you can make a semi-private pop in and out.

name: Pagliacci Pizza
directions: Walk through the entrance, go to the hallway at the far left of the dining area - bathrooms are on the right side of the hallway.
comment: Completely unisex bathrooms, although only one has a tampon garbage (the one farthest from the entry). Regulars still generally act like they're gendered though, so don't be surprised if some cis women refuse to use the bathroom without the tampon bin.

name: Target
directions: take a left when you walk in and look for double doors that say "office" on them, there is a restroom for guests and staff through the doors on the right

name: Starbucks Drive Thru
directions: Walking though the main door, there is a hallway on the right with two bathrooms - both gender neutral

name: Lisser Hall / Mills College
directions: Just nod to the gate guard as you go in, they won't stop you. Go straight down the main road till it makes a T-junction. Lisser is the white building on the right hand side of the path.

name: Carmen Flores Recreation Center / Josie de la Cruz Park
Harris-Millis Dining
directions: There are three gender neutral bathrooms by the back left of the dining hall, near the elevator.

name: Charity's'Bakery and Cafe
directions: Just off of Broad st, the second building on the right. There are 2 bathrooms in the back.
comment: Coffee shop style. So you could probably just asks the workers and they won't care. They are nice, but expensive.

name: Wayne State Stufent Center Lobby
directions: Across from Mad Anthony's (general store) down the hall away from the food court. Marked by a sign, before the front desk, 1st floor.

name: Chevron
directions: Use the second door all the way around back after getting the key.
comment: Be a paying customer.

directions: In the back, not the first door.

name: Creamistry

comment: Just walk in no key needed

name: China King

comment: All bathrooms have baby changing stations!

name: Utah Valley University
